summary: This is an FBI evidence inventory cover sheet documenting the migration and acquisition of telephone CDs and a subpoena related to the Alfredo Rodriguez case, sent to FBI Headquarters for a BALEEN data sweep. It appears to be part of evidence handling in the Epstein investigation.

persons.name: Alfredo Rodriguez
persons.context: His case is referenced in connection with telephone CDs and a subpoena that were acquired and sent to FBI HQ for a BALEEN data sweep.

events.title: Evidence acquisition and migration
events.description: Telephone CDs and a subpoena related to the Alfredo Rodriguez case were acquired and migrated as part of evidence handling, and sent to FBI Headquarters for a BALEEN data sweep.

keyFacts: Telephone CDs and a subpoena related to Alfredo Rodriguez's case were acquired by the FBI on June 23, 2010.
The evidence was sent to FBI Headquarters for a BALEEN data sweep, indicating a digital forensic analysis.
The document is an evidence inventory cover sheet, showing formal handling of materials in the Epstein investigation.
